<div id="review_3010588599" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3010588599" />
    <a title="Akhila Pai Dhamotharan" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1382515-akhila-pai-dhamotharan"><img alt="Akhila Pai Dhamotharan" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1514750450p2/1382515.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3010588599?book_show_action=true">Oct 27, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Akhila Pai Dhamotharan" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Akhila Pai Dhamotharan" href="/user/show/1382515-akhila-pai-dhamotharan">Akhila Pai Dhamotharan</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3010588599" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4796930018726013055">Everyone in today’s day &amp; age needs to read this book! Given how much we hear about &amp; how lightly everyone talks about being depressed and given how much we conceal about our mental health issues from our family &amp; friends for fear of being ostracised, it means that the only people we are willing to talk to about this are psychiatrists.<br/><br/>But are psychiatrists working with our interests in mind? or are they working on furthering their own &amp; their Institution’s riches by conniving with the pharmaceut</span>
  <span id="freeText4796930018726013055" style="display:none">Everyone in today’s day &amp; age needs to read this book! Given how much we hear about &amp; how lightly everyone talks about being depressed and given how much we conceal about our mental health issues from our family &amp; friends for fear of being ostracised, it means that the only people we are willing to talk to about this are psychiatrists.<br /><br />But are psychiatrists working with our interests in mind? or are they working on furthering their own &amp; their Institution’s riches by conniving with the pharmaceutical industry? <br /><br />While I could stomach stories about the Pharma industry suppressing data about negative drug trials, about the total inefficacy of anti-depressants &amp; anti-psychotic drugs and many more unholy stories in the book, what I could not stomach was the flimsy “scientific“ basis of this entire medical specialisation called Psychiatry!! <br /><br />I could not believe that people in committees decided &amp; added mental disorders to a list (with no scientific justification or research!) called DSM that doctors across the world referenced to diagnose patients!! With every edition of the DSM, more disorders are getting added making it more &amp; more difficult to be normal anymore! <br /><br />And the implications of the terrible foundation of this “medical science” ? - More children being diagnosed with ADHD, women diagnosed with pre-menstrual disorder (eye roll!) and at least 1 in 4 of us being mental unwell!<br /><br />The medicalisation of misery was a horror to read, Psychiatric imperialism just broke my heart (where this half baked, proven-Unsuccessful method is being exported to all parts of the world by deep pocketed Pharma companies) and the scant science (in the true sense of the word) in Psychiatry made this every page of this book a terrifying read! <br /><br />If you or a loved one is suffering a mental illness, definitely read this book &amp; please look out for alternative therapies in addition to working with a psychiatrist who is aware of these problems! The book suggests that a person-centric model where the family &amp; friends work with the patient and doctor show the best results.<br /><br /><br /><br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="4796930018726013055" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


