<div id="review_752244657" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/752244657" />
    <a title="Lesley Fulford" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/25156715-lesley-fulford"><img alt="Lesley Fulford" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1383086271p2/25156715.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/752244657?book_show_action=true">Oct 29, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Lesley Fulford" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Lesley Fulford" href="/user/show/25156715-lesley-fulford">Lesley Fulford</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer752244657" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10012412157489310610">What to say about this book........<br/><br/>There are a number of points well made however I think Ben goldacre makes them in a slightly slicker fashion. Whilst putting forward some thought provoking ideas the book only rants against psychiatry, completely un acknowledging of the fact that psychotherapy isn&apos;t any better than drug treatment or placebo either. This turned into a anti psychiatry book when in fact the issues raised are not always unique to psychiatry. <br/><br/>I feel this book had a predetermined out</span>
  <span id="freeText10012412157489310610" style="display:none">What to say about this book........<br /><br />There are a number of points well made however I think Ben goldacre makes them in a slightly slicker fashion. Whilst putting forward some thought provoking ideas the book only rants against psychiatry, completely un acknowledging of the fact that psychotherapy isn't any better than drug treatment or placebo either. This turned into a anti psychiatry book when in fact the issues raised are not always unique to psychiatry. <br /><br />I feel this book had a predetermined outcome from the beginning so was not a book about psychiatry but about why it is evil. Sad really as it fails to recognise the extremely positive impact psychiatry has had in many individuals lives. </span>
  <a data-text-id="10012412157489310610" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

