    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3561676101" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3561676101" />
    <a title="An Te" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/15827252-an-te"><img alt="An Te" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1492634570p2/15827252.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3561676101?book_show_action=true">Sep 25, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="An Te" class="user" itemprop="url" name="An Te" href="/user/show/15827252-an-te">An Te</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/23945066-cracked">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3561676101" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3527879384664768731">This is not sedate review. It packs bunch from the word go and defends the thesis that psychiatry is pseudoscience founded on the false worldview of mental illness as physical disease. It simply is not the case and James Davies really does a splendid job to present the lay of the land of psychiatry using all his journalistic skills. The four pillars of the book are dated from Davies as follows.<br/><br/>1. Psychiatry needs to develop greater modesty and humility about what it can actually hope to achieve.</span>
  <span id="freeText3527879384664768731" style="display:none">This is not sedate review. It packs bunch from the word go and defends the thesis that psychiatry is pseudoscience founded on the false worldview of mental illness as physical disease. It simply is not the case and James Davies really does a splendid job to present the lay of the land of psychiatry using all his journalistic skills. The four pillars of the book are dated from Davies as follows.<br /><br />1. Psychiatry needs to develop greater modesty and humility about what it can actually hope to achieve. (And I would add that its evidenced needs to correspond with its theory. James advocates this throughout. Why use a theory which isn't veridical?) <br /><br />2. There needs to be more thorough regulation and transparency regarding psychiatry’s financial ties to the pharmaceutical industry. (Right on the money here. Transparency is the key word.) <br /><br />3. The training of future psychiatrists must include instilling greater critical awareness of psychiatry’s scientific failings and current excesses, as well as better awareness of how to manage patients outside of the medical model. (I would have been more prescriptive that psychiatrists become better trained in philosophy, religion and logical argument. It will serve them well when talking to patients.)<br /><br />4. The public needs to become better informed about the current crisis in psychiatry. And if the industry does not reform, people need to be prepared to vote with their feet.<br /><br />It was a book I warmed to especially when he reached the point of interviewing the top echelon of institutional psychiatry in the UK. What was found there was shocking, and James worked out on his feet what would and would not work. All in all, an honest account of psychiatry. It would have been nice to discuss aspects of religion and how they conceive of mental health... But James Davies is well aware he's only touching the surface on questions he raises. A humble presentation.</span>
  <a data-text-id="3527879384664768731" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


