    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2029297873" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2029297873" />
    <a title="William Nist" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/18846038-william-nist"><img alt="William Nist" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1420132384p2/18846038.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2029297873?book_show_action=true">Jun 14, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="William Nist" class="user" itemprop="url" name="William Nist" href="/user/show/18846038-william-nist">William Nist</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9781605984735" href="/book/show/16255227-cracked">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/18846038-william-nist?shelf=medical">medical</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2029297873" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12100812669912355480">CRACKED is a critique of the &apos;medical model&apos; dominant in modern psychiatry. The author questions not only the efficacy of psychotropic pharmaceuticals, but the legitimacy of the very diagnostic system (DSM) used in prescribing these medications, not to mention the vested interest that pharmaceutical companies have in the sale of these medications. The author laments the lack of science behind the use of these drugs, the over medicalizing of normal human experience, and the one tract medical educ</span>
  <span id="freeText12100812669912355480" style="display:none">CRACKED is a critique of the 'medical model' dominant in modern psychiatry. The author questions not only the efficacy of psychotropic pharmaceuticals, but the legitimacy of the very diagnostic system (DSM) used in prescribing these medications, not to mention the vested interest that pharmaceutical companies have in the sale of these medications. The author laments the lack of science behind the use of these drugs, the over medicalizing of normal human experience, and the one tract medical education employed in the training of future psychiatrists. <br /><br />Dr Davies, who is a psychiatrist of the psychoanalytical bent, prescribes a more holistic but cautious approach to the handling of human distress, and a rebellion by patients against the use of ineffective drugs in treating what amounts to normal human experience. <br /><br />From my personal experience with SSRI's, the distress of human life was subdued and sublimated through some alteration of my consciousness, but the placid emotional state took away any passion that served to propel my enthusiasm for life...not to mention I gained 35 pounds! Davies claims that these drugs work no better than placebo (their success is ONLY through the placebo effect!), and the aforementioned side effects are the most notable result of treatment. <br /><br />An important viewpoint that must be considered individuals and society.<br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="12100812669912355480" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

